%section#services_new.services
  %h1 New account
  %div
    %h3 This authentication is new to Omniauth pure
    %p.small
      Provider: #{@authhash[:provider]}
      %br/
      ID: #{@authhash[:uid]}
      %br/
      Name: #{@authhash[:name]}
      %br/
      Email: #{@authhash[:email]}
      %br/
    = form_tag :controller => "services", :action => "newaccount" do
      = submit_tag "Confirm and create new account"
      = submit_tag "Cancel"
  %p
    If you think you already have an Omniauth pure account, and you were just trying to associate a new authentication with your existing account, then you’re in the wrong place. You’re not logged into Omniauth pure right now.
  %p.small.nomargin
    If you have a Omniauth pure account, and you’d like to associate another authentication with it, here’s what to do:
  %ul.small
    %li Log in in to Omniauth pure with your existing authentication service TODO
    %li
      Go to your settings page (located at the top/right corner of the page)
    %li Add one or more accounts to be used to sign-in